[3] Canada (Quebec/Lanaudiere)
Date: Tue 10 Mar 2015
Source: CJADNews [edited]
http://www.cjad.com/cjad-news/2015/03/10/measles-outbreak-grows-in-lanaudiere


Public health officials in the Lanaudiere, northeast of Montreal, say there are now 80 confirmed cases of measles across the region. That's up from 10 cases just a month ago, and 25 cases less than 2 weeks ago. Health officials say the rapid spread comes as no surprise because the people who have become infected had not been vaccinated and were being followed closely because of the expectation that they would eventually contract the disease.

The outbreak was touched off in early February 2015 with the return of 10 people from 2 families who had traveled to Disneyland in California.

[Byline: Andrew Peplowski]

